You should presently be a senior in high school;
Or be transitioning from high school to a college or university;
Or be already enrolled in a college or university inside the United States or Canada.

Legal resident of the 50 U.S. states or District of Columbia as a U.S. citizen, a U.S. permanent resident or an international student that has a valid student visa (F-1 visa) to study in the U.S. DACA recipients are not eligible;
Age 18 or older
Pursuing an Associate Degree, Bachelor’s Degree, Master’s Degree, or Doctor of Philosophy (PhD) at an accredited U.S. college or university located in the 50 U.S. states or District of Columbia with a cumulative college GPA of 3.0 or greater on a 4.0 scale. Students enrolled in certificate programs only are not eligible;
Declared major of biology, chemistry, biochemistry or a related life science field.
Students with a declared major outside of the life sciences but are pursuing a life science minor are not eligible.
